 Yes, we can use JSON to help structure and manage our form data in several key ways. Based on our documentation, here's how we can use JSON:

1. Form Configuration:
```javascript
const formConfig = {
  "fields": [
    {
      "id": "projectName",
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Project Name",
      "validation": {
        "type": "TEXT_LENGTH",
        "min": 3,
        "max": 50,
        "errorMessage": "Project name must be between 3-50 characters"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "shopPartner",
      "type": "dropdown",
      "title": "Shop Partner",
      "sourceSheet": "ShopPartners",
      "sourceColumn": "Name",
      "filterActive": true,
      "dependencies": [] 
    },
    {
      "id": "industry",
      "type": "dropdown",
      "title": "Industry Category",
      "sourceSheet": "Industries",
      "sourceColumn": "IndustryName",
      "includeOther": true,
      "dependencies": [
        {
          "field": "customCategory",
          "showWhen": "Other"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

2. Form Response Data Structure:
```javascript
const projectData = {
  "id": "P2402-001",
  "submissionDate": "2025-02-12T10:00:00Z",
  "projectData": {
    "name": "Workshop Project A",
    "partner": "PT001",
    "lead": "PL001",
    "dates": {
      "start": "2025-02-15T09:00:00Z",
      "end": "2025-02-28T17:00:00Z"
    },
    "classification": {
      "priority": "High",
      "status": "Not Started",
      "industry": "Manufacturing"
    },
    "requirements": {
      "description": "Project description here",
      "budget": 5000,
      "teamSize": 3
    }
  }
}
```

3. Validation Rules:
```javascript
const validationRules = {
  "projectName": {
    "type": "TEXT_LENGTH",
    "min": 3,
    "max": 50,
    "message": "Project name must be between 3-50 characters"
  },
  "dates": {
    "type": "DATE_RANGE",
    "rules": [
      {
        "check": "startBeforeEnd",
        "message": "Start date must be before end date"
      },
      {
        "check": "notPast",
        "message": "Start date cannot be in the past"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Using JSON this way provides several benefits:
1. Easier to maintain and update form structure
2. Cleaner data transformation between form and spreadsheet
3. More organized validation rules
4. Better handling of dependencies between fields

Would you like me to show how to implement any of these JSON structures in our form creation code?

